# Delta for admin-dashboard

## ADDED Requirements

### Requirement: Must-have admin workflow completeness
The system MUST provide operational UI flows (not placeholder/shell-only views) for Products, Categories, Orders, and Catalog Jobs using existing admin endpoints only.

#### Scenario: Admin completes primary workflow navigation
- GIVEN an authenticated admin user opens `/admin`
- WHEN the user navigates to Products, Categories, Orders, and Catalog Jobs
- THEN each section renders actionable list/detail or operation views
- AND no section shows placeholder-only content for these four workflows

#### Scenario: Empty state remains operational
- GIVEN a workflow has no records
- WHEN the admin opens that workflow view
- THEN the UI shows a valid empty state with available next actions

### Requirement: No-new-domain boundary for dashboard polish
The system SHALL NOT introduce new admin business domains in this change and MUST limit scope to products, categories, orders, and catalog jobs.

#### Scenario: Out-of-scope domain is not added
- GIVEN this change is under review
- WHEN admin routes and navigation are validated
- THEN no new domain areas (for example customers/promotions/analytics) are present

# Delta for admin-auth-access

## ADDED Requirements

### Requirement: Backend-authoritative admin access guard
The system MUST determine admin access from backend-authenticated session/role truth and MUST NOT rely on client-only persisted role flags as the source of truth.

#### Scenario: Refresh preserves true admin access
- GIVEN an admin has a valid authenticated backend session
- WHEN the admin refreshes or directly loads an admin URL
- THEN access is granted based on backend role response

#### Scenario: Non-admin or unauthenticated user is blocked deterministically
- GIVEN a user without valid admin authorization
- WHEN the user requests an admin route
- THEN unauthenticated users receive login redirect/entry UX
- AND unauthorized users receive explicit forbidden UX (403)

### Requirement: Explicit login/logout UX state transitions
The system MUST provide explicit admin login/logout UX transitions and SHALL clear stale client state on logout.

#### Scenario: Logout invalidates admin access state
- GIVEN an authenticated admin in admin UI
- WHEN the admin logs out
- THEN admin routes become inaccessible until re-authenticated
- AND any cached client-side access marker is cleared

# Delta for catalog-job-operations

## ADDED Requirements

### Requirement: Catalog job operator action closure
The system MUST NOT expose broken catalog-job actions; cancel MUST either work end-to-end with backend contract or be presented as clearly non-actionable.

#### Scenario: Supported cancel executes successfully
- GIVEN a cancelable catalog job and supported backend cancel contract
- WHEN operator triggers cancel
- THEN job state updates to reflect cancel outcome

#### Scenario: Unsupported cancel is non-actionable
- GIVEN cancel is not supported end-to-end
- WHEN operator views job actions
- THEN cancel is hidden or disabled with clear status

### Requirement: Operational diagnostics visibility
The system MUST surface job row/report errors and actionable status details needed for operator triage.

#### Scenario: Operator sees actionable error context
- GIVEN a catalog job with row or report failures
- WHEN operator opens job details
- THEN the UI presents error diagnostics and status context sufficient to choose next action
